(41, 8, 22, 41, 2, 3, 3, 'bring a blind man unto him', 'Healing of the Afflicted', 'Both passages emphasize the act of bringing someone in need of healing to Jesus. In Mark 8:22, a blind man is brought to Jesus, while in Mark 2:3, a paralyzed man is carried by four individuals, showcasing the communal effort in seeking Jesus for healing.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 8, 22, 43, 1, 44, 44, 'Bethsaida', 'Connection through Bethsaida', 'Both passages emphasize Bethsaida, linking the location of a miracle with the origin of Philip, Andrew, and Peter. This connection highlights the significance of Bethsaida in the ministry of Jesus and the early disciples.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 8, 22, 43, 12, 21, 21, 'Bethsaida', 'Connection through Bethsaida', 'Both passages emphasize Bethsaida as a significant location. In Mark, a blind man is brought to Jesus in Bethsaida, while in John, individuals from Bethsaida seek to see Jesus.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
